                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable S</hi> 180.) I took the prisoner into custody in Edmund-street, Battle-bridge, between seven and eight o'clock on the morning of the 25th of August—I said, "Mr. Crosier wishes to speak with you"—he said, "Yes, I know what it is about, I will call as soon as I have had my breakfast"—I said, "You had better go with me now"—he said, "Very well, I will go with you"—on the road he said, "This is a bad job, but I intended calling and paying him the money, I was intoxicated when I did it"—he asked what I thought be would be done to—I said I could not say (<hi rend="italic">order read</hi>.)</p>
